 {"id":"bd-mzct","title":"Add unit tests for Ext4Superblock query methods in ffs-ondisk","description":"The ffs-ondisk ext4.rs module has 206 tests but several Ext4Superblock query methods are tested only through the ffs-ext4 facade. Add direct unit tests in ffs-ondisk/src/ext4.rs for: parse_from_image, has_compat/has_incompat/has_ro_compat, is_64bit, group_desc_size, groups_count, has_metadata_csum, csum_seed, validate_checksum, validate_geometry, validate_v1, feature_diagnostics_v1, group_desc_offset, inode_table_offset, locate_inode, inode_device_offset. These tests complement the facade tests already added in ffs-ext4.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-26T03:23:28.818125035Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-26T03:35:03.599721597Z","closed_at":"2026-02-26T03:35:03.599691791Z","close_reason":"Added 25 unit tests for Ext4Superblock query methods in ffs-ondisk/src/ext4.rs: has_compat, has_incompat, has_ro_compat, is_64bit, group_desc_size, groups_count, has_metadata_csum, csum_seed, validate_checksum, group_desc_offset, inode_table_offset, parse_from_image. All 293 tests pass, clippy clean, fmt clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ondisk","quality","tests"]}
 {"id":"bd-n3s3","title":"ffs-cli fails to compile due to missing ioctl_trace_path field","description":"In crates/ffs-cli/src/main.rs, MountOptions is initialized without the recently added ioctl_trace_path field, causing E0063 compilation errors.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-18T16:50:51.015872536Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-18T17:17:04.588931935Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T17:17:04.586214758Z","close_reason":"Verified: ffs-cli MountOptions initializers include ioctl_trace_path; rch cargo check -p ffs-cli passes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-n5l9","title":"Align ffs-core durability autopilot floor with ffs-repair policy","description":"ffs-core::DurabilityAutopilot currently accepts/chooses 1% repair overhead (1.01 multiplier), but ffs-repair::autopilot defaults to a 3%-10% search range. This cross-crate drift lets the public RepairPolicy surface undercut the actual repair policy floor. Raise the ffs-core autopilot minimum candidate/default range to 3%-10%, update public docs/comments, and adjust facade/core tests accordingly. Acceptance: ffs-core/ffs tests reflect [1.03, 1.10] bounds and targeted rch check/test pass.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:38:13.252142493Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T20:45:28.388823859Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T20:45:28.388554659Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-n73h4","title":"Reject oversized ext4 inline-data inode sizes","description":"Fresh-eyes ext4 inline-data follow-up: read_ext4_inline_data caps reads by assembled inline_data.len(), so an inode whose i_size exceeds i_block + system.data capacity silently returns a short read despite the comment saying it pads. Inline-data ext4 files should fit in inline storage; reject this malformed metadata instead of truncating or zero-padding it.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-27T08:59:37.740402051Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T09:04:27.057342881Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T09:04:27.055390923Z","close_reason":"Ext4 inline-data reads now reject i_size values larger than assembled inline capacity instead of silently short-reading or zero-padding malformed metadata; added focused oversized-capacity regression. Validation passed: focused ffs-core inline-data regressions, fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, workspace check, and workspace clippy.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-n8blq","title":"Conformance harness: build syscall-level conformance tests vs reference fs","description":"Apply /testing-conformance-harnesses skill. Build a conformance test that drives our fs through the same syscall sequences as a reference (Linux ext4 in tmpfs). Differential diff outputs per syscall (return value, errno, side effects). Cover: file lifecycle, directory ops, attribute ops, link semantics, mmap interaction, fsync semantics, mount/umount.","notes":"2026-04-26 cod-fs: extended syscall conformance matrix with reference/FUSE differential negative errno contracts for mkdir(EEXIST), unlink/rename(ENOENT), and rmdir(ENOTEMPTY); added reference-only regression guard. 2026-04-26 cod-fs: added fd metadata syscall coverage for fchmod, ftruncate, fstat, fsync, and path stat equivalence; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS, targeted reference probes, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: extended syscall differential harness with symlink fstatat/readlinkat/O_NOFOLLOW contracts and a reference regression guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probes, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit 9bd9141 pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added truncate-extension zero-fill coverage to the syscall differential harness with reference guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probe group, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit 75ad9f8 pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added open-unlink fd lifetime coverage to the syscall differential harness with reference guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probe group, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit efe814e pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added open-rename fd lifetime coverage to the syscall differential harness with reference guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probe group, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit 0e52f66 pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added dirfd mutation coverage for openat/mkdirat/renameat/unlinkat/rmdir through the syscall differential harness with reference guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probe, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit 3f487b7 pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added rename-over-existing-file replacement coverage to the syscall differential harness with reference guard; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probe, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit 121eb39 pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: aligned mounted renameat2 conformance with current implementation: ext4 now asserts RENAME_NOREPLACE success/EEXIST and RENAME_EXCHANGE swap, while btrfs asserts RENAME_NOREPLACE success/EEXIST and RENAME_EXCHANGE EINVAL/no drift; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, focused ext4/btrfs FUSE tests compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit c645a29 pushed to main and mirrored to master. 2026-04-27 cod-fs: added renameat2 RENAME_NOREPLACE and RENAME_EXCHANGE coverage to the syscall differential script with a reference guard and unavailable-kernel skip path; validation passed with fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, reference probe, FUSE differential compile/soft-skip, workspace check, and workspace clippy; commit 0a800f5 pushed to main and mirrored to master.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:22:37.099317207Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T05:15:46Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T05:15:46Z","close_reason":"Completed syscall-level conformance harness covering lifecycle, directory, attribute, link/symlink, mmap, fsync, mount-backed differential behavior, negative errno, open fd lifetime, rename replacement, and renameat2 contracts. Latest validation passed fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, focused reference/FUSE probes, workspace check, and workspace clippy.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
